OL,3,CMedics guilty of failing to care for
OL,4,Cman who died from cardiac arrest
OL,6,FTwo members of Jersey's Ambulance
OL,7,FService have been found guilty of
OL,8,Ffailing to adequately care for a man
OL,9,Fin the moments before he died.
OL,11,FParamedic John Sutherland, 61, and
OL,12,Fambulance technician Tom Le Sauteur,
OL,13,F36, faced one count each of breaching
OL,14,Fhealth and safety law in Jersey - they
OL,15,Fhad both denied the charge.
OL,17,FFollowing an eight-day trial, jurats
OL,18,Ffound the pair had failed to carry out
OL,19,Ftheir duties to protect Frazer Irvine
OL,20,Fwho died from a cardiac arrest in
OL,21,FMarch 2022.
